 "You ruined everything good always said you were misunderstood" She always made it seem like I was the insensitive one and never cared about her feelings when it's not true. I accepted, better than before, that she would never be the mother I wanted her to be, but I was also not the daughter she wanted me to be.

I know people usually think of their toxic exes but this song reminds me of my mom. Especially the second part of the song. 

The line "I don't relate to you cause I'd never treat me this shitty you make me hate this city" During this pandemic she made me feel suffocated every time I am with her. It made me want to run away and go back to Japan and leave her here. I don't want her to come with me and I feel horrible for thinking this way but I want her to disappear from my life

The line "Never told anyone anything bad" I talk about my problems with my mom with my friends but I always say "I understand her" or "I still love her" but when she talks about me with her friends she never says anything good. She tells her friends about our fights how I'm "lazy", "deaf" and always complain. Now, I'm just sick of it I don't want to understand her anymore if she can't do the same thing for me.

The line "You were my everything and all you did was make me fucking sad" resonated with me because I love my mom the most. She is my number one person since I didn't grow up with my dad. I could take any insults when it came from someone else but when she says it, it hurts more than anything. 

"So don't waste the time I don't have and don't try to make me feel bad" I am done understanding her and putting her feelings first. I am so done with being accused of being insensitive and selfish when she only ever thought about herself and her feelings in every situation. She never ever tried to understand my feelings. I'm so done with her making it seem like I'm the bad guy, blaming everything on me.

 "You ruined everything good always said you were misunderstood" She always made it seem like I was the insensitive one and never cared about her feelings when it's not true. When I wanted to dia and she saw my suicide note instead of thinking about my feelings she got mad at me because I wasn't "appreciative of her enough." I remember feeling guilty for thinking that way and apologizing multiple times. Now, looking back, I don't know why I had to say sorry for being depressed and feeling that way. She should've, no I wanted her to comfort me and reassured me that she loved me. Not get mad.


"Just fucking leave me alone" Now this is what I feel about her. I love you mom but I think if I were to spend one more moment with you, I'd die. I don't think you really love me, every time you look at me you only see my father. You compare me to him. You say I'm just like him. How can that happen? I lived with you all my life. I hate you mom but I don't want to, but sometimes that's just how I feel.
